text.section:
The council shall:
Advise the cabinet on administration of the local health department personnel program pursuant to KRS Chapter 212;
Hear appeals from:
Applicants for positions for which examinations are being or have been conducted;
Eligible applicants on examination registers; and
Classified employees who have been dismissed, demoted, or suspended for cause;
Hear appeals regarding discrimination in a personnel action involving an agency employee or an applicant for employment;
Make an annual report to the department and agency; and
Consider and act upon matters that may be referred to the council by the department.
